data.title: Visitor Information & Reviews
data.meta_description: Drøbak Aquarium is a museum in Drøbak. View visitor information, information about the collection and read reviews.
data.text:
With an annual footfall of approximately 35,000 visitors, Drøbak Aquarium is a popular destination for tourists and locals alike. The aquarium is designed to be child-friendly, making it an ideal place for family outings.

Marine Life at Drøbak Aquarium

Drøbak Aquarium is home to 14 aquariums, 2 large tanks, and a touch pool, housing a variety of sea creatures. Visitors can observe common fish species found in Norwegian waters, including eels, catfish, and some shark species, as well as various types of shellfish, mussels, echinoderms, sea anemones, and starfish.
